# Storefront checkout and payments

- Apply only to `storefront/src/modules/checkout/**`. Complement Stripe’s general best practices (user/plugin skills) with Medusa-specific flow in this app.
- Keep card and payment method entry inside Stripe or PayPal’s official client components; never log or persist raw card numbers, CVC, or other PCI-sensitive data in application logs or your own API payloads.
- Rely on Medusa’s payment collection and session completion patterns already wired in the checkout (create/update payment sessions, then complete the cart) rather than ad hoc charges from the client.
- Use `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` only for publishable keys and URLs the browser must know; all server-to-server or admin credentials stay in server env vars.
- If you change the payment wrapper under `storefront/src/modules/checkout/components/payment-wrapper/`, keep Stripe.js and PayPal script loading and error boundaries aligned with the existing components so the checkout can recover from provider failures with clear user messaging.
